div1.p:




      JOHN DUKE
 (City Policeman SOS
). On 3rd February I took the prisoner in custody on London Bridge—his wife pointed him out to me—he was wheeling a barrow—he saw her speak to me, and left his barrow and ran away—I caught him—his wife came up, and he said "You are b----clever; you were going to have me in a day."
